DATA MODELS (models/)

  menu-item.model.ts
    CrudAction        : 'c' | 'r' | 'u' | 'd'
    MenuItem {
      ItemID, ItemKey, ItemName, ItemDescription, ItemCategory
      ItemPrice, ItemPriceString, ItemCost, ItemImage, ItemBadge
      IsAvailable, IsActive, PreparationTime, Calories
    }
    MenuItemPayload   : Partial<MenuItem> & { ItemID?: number }

  order-list-item.model.ts
    OrderStatus       : 'pending' | 'complete' | 'confirmed' | 'ready' | 'preparing'
    OrderListItem {
      OrderID, OrderNumber, StatusCode, StatusName
      CustomerName, CustomerPhone, CustomerEmail
      OrderType, OrderNotes
      SubTotal, TaxAmount, DiscountAmount, TotalAmount, ItemCount
      ItemID, ItemName, ItemCategory, UnitPrice, Quantity, LineTotal
      ConfirmedAt, CompletedAt, CancelledAt, CreatedAt, UpdatedAt
      SpecialInstructions
    }
    OrderHeadDetail   : header-only variant of above
    OrderFullDetailResponse : head + line items

SERVICES (services/)

  auth.guard.ts
    Strategy          : localStorage token ('authToken') presence check
    Logout            : static AuthGuard.logout() clears token + sets isLoggedOut flag
    Post-login redirect: stores attempted URL in localStorage('postLoginRedirect')

  menu.service.ts
    getMenuItems()    : GET  CRUD_ReadALL — falls back to mock if API fails
    mutateMenuItem()  : POST CRUD + action query param ('c','r','u','d')
    updateMenuItem()  : validates ItemID, applies mock update or calls mutateMenuItem('u')
    normalizeApiPayload(): handles both array and wrapped-object API responses

  menubv.service.ts   : BV location menu variant — read/write pattern mirrors menu.service
  menups.service.ts   : PS location menu variant — read/write pattern mirrors menu.service

  orders-list.service.ts
    getOrdersByStatus(status) : GET  Get_OrdersbyStatus?status=STATUS
    getOrderByIdFull(orderId) : GET  Get_OrderbyOrderIdFull_HeadandDetails?OrderId=ID
    updateOrderStatus(id, status): POST Update_OrderStatus { OrderID, StatusCode }
    StatusCode mapping : first char uppercase + rest lowercase

PAGE COMPONENTS (pages/)

  login/
    LoginComponent      — Authentication form, writes authToken to localStorage

  overview/
    OverviewComponent   — KPI metrics, activity feed, readiness checks, pipeline stages
    Metrics:
      Kitchen throughput: 312 plates/hr  (+8% vs yesterday)
      Delivery promise  : 24 min avg     (-2 min vs target)
      Customer sentiment: 4.82 ★
      Inventory buffer  : 3.4 hrs
    Readiness checks    : line cooks, courier capacity, menu QA, promo assets
    Kitchen pipeline    : Prep > Cooking > Packaging > Courier handoff

  menu-manager/
    MenuManagerComponent — Inventory grid, upcoming drops, bulk utilities

  menu-list/
    MenuListComponent   — Live editable table of all menu items
    EditableRow extends MenuItem with: dirty, saving, rowError, rowSuccess flags
    Inline save per row using menuService.updateMenuItem()
    Signal-based state  : loading, error, rows (Angular signals)
    trackByRow          : tracks by ItemID

  menu-listps/
    MenuListpsComponent — PS location variant of menu list (mirrors menu-list)

  menu-listbv/
    MenuListbvComponent — BV location variant of menu list (mirrors menu-list)

  marketing/
    MarketingComponent  — Campaign pacing, channel insights, active push tracking

  orders/
    OrdersComponent     — Live fulfillment timeline, zone capacity board

  orders-list/
    OrdersListComponent
      Status filter     : pending / complete / confirmed / ready / preparing
      Signal state      : selectedStatus, loading, error, orders, selectedOrder
      Computed signals  : totalOrders, totalItems, totalSales
      On status change  : reloads order list via ordersListService.getOrdersByStatus()
    OrderDetailComponent
      Sub-component for expanded order detail view within orders-list page
    StatusChangeComponent
      Inline status mutation — calls ordersListService.updateOrderStatus()

  customers/
    CustomersComponent
      Segments:
        Total Customers   : 200 count, +14% month
        Regular Customers : 37 count,  +6% month
        Weekly Mailing    : 180 count,  +3% month
      Voice feed (guest feedback + action items): 3 entries
    CustomerComponent     — Browse/search all customers (customer-list route)
    CustDetailComponent   — Individual customer detail view

  settings/
    SettingsComponent     — Automation rules, access overview

MOCK DATA (mocks/)
  mock-menu-items.ts    — Static array of MenuItem objects used when
                          environment.useMockMenuApi = true or API is unreachable

API ENDPOINTS AT LAUNCH
  Menu Read All         : https://api.getgogi.com/api/CMSDemo/Menu/CRUD_ReadALL
  Menu CRUD             : https://api.getgogi.com/api/CMSDemo/Menu/CRUD
  Orders by Status      : https://api.getgogi.com/api/CMSDemo/Orders/Get_OrdersbyStatus
  Order Full Detail     : https://api.getgogi.com/api/CMSDemo/Orders/Get_OrderbyOrderIdFull_HeadandDetails
  Order Status Update   : https://api.getgogi.com/api/CMSDemo/Orders/Update_OrderStatus

BUILD / SCRIPTS
  npm start             — dev server at http://localhost:4200 with API proxy
  npm run build         — production build to dist/
  npm test              — Karma unit tests
  npm run watch         — build in watch mode

DEPLOY NOTES
  web.config included for IIS deployment (URL rewrite for SPA routing)
  proxy.conf.json routes /api/* calls in dev to avoid CORS issues

